{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":118263,"duration_api_ms":158752,"num_turns":5,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"990d3e42-882a-4dd6-8749-4d8a64e92457","total_cost_usd":0.44342475,"usage":{"input_tokens":1207,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30405,"cache_read_input_tokens":83871,"output_tokens":3358,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":30405,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":867,"outputTokens":7383,"cacheReadInputTokens":275335,"cacheCreationInputTokens":44926,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.12147300000000001,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000},"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":1207,"outputTokens":3358,"cacheReadInputTokens":83871,"cacheCreationInputTokens":30405,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.32195175,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"summary":"All six amendments are verified against the codebase and identify real issues. Three amendments (a8837f43, cd84c211, 9910b1f5) address the same fundamental spec-conformance gap from different angles — the implementation deliberately kept run_id and plan_hash as Option<&str> with enhanced backfill/provenance logic, directly contradicting the spec's requirement to make them required and remove runless/backfill code. The remaining three (33dc0ec6, 20d95d35, 0b8774c0) identify independent architectural and safety issues that stand on their own merits regardless of the spec question.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-19-a8837f43","decision":"accept","rationale":"Fully verified. Both run_id and plan_hash remain Option<&str> in TaskRunLineagePort (service.rs:103-104,117-118) and in record_bead_start (service.rs:409-410). The runless matching code (find_matching_running_task_run with .or_else() fallback at model.rs:495-500, unique_terminal_replay_match runless guards at fs.rs:2829+) was enhanced rather than removed. safe_plan_hash_backfill, snapshot_plan_hash, and the snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation field were added rather than removed. The comment at fs.rs:2609 explicitly states 'Deliberate deviation from Issue 3 acceptance criteria.' The implementation chose a provenance-tracking approach — arguably defensible engineering — but directly contradicts the spec. The amendment correctly demands resolution: either amend the spec to accept this approach, or rework the implementation to match."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-33dc0ec6","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. snapshot_plan_hash at fs.rs:2555 calls FsMilestoneSnapshotStore.read_snapshot() directly on the unit-type adapter, bypassing the MilestoneSnapshotPort abstraction that the service layer uses. This couples two adapters that should be independent under hexagonal architecture. If tests or a future backend use a different MilestoneSnapshotPort implementation, the lineage store silently reads from filesystem snapshots anyway. The fix is straightforward: either inject the snapshot reader as a dependency, or have the service layer pass the plan_hash down to the lineage store."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-20d95d35","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. At fs.rs:3403-3416, safe_plan_hash_backfill MUST be called before entry.outcome = outcome because the backfill's is_terminal() guard (fs.rs:~2593) would skip already-terminal entries. A 12-line comment documents this invariant, but comments are not enforcement. If the two adjacent lines are reordered during refactoring, plan_hash backfill silently and permanently stops working on finalization — no error, no test failure, no diagnostic. Either a finalize_entry helper that enforces the ordering structurally, or a regression test that detects ordering violations, would prevent this latent defect from manifesting."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-0b8774c0","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. At fs.rs:2839-2856, unique_terminal_replay_match uses AppError::CorruptRecord for the case where requested_run_id is Some but requested_started_at is None. The inline comment explicitly acknowledges 'This is an internal programming error (caller violated the API contract), NOT corrupt on-disk data' and then says 'adding a dedicated variant is not warranted.' Using CorruptRecord for an API contract violation conflates two fundamentally different failure modes during operator triage — one triggers data recovery investigation, the other triggers code review. A dedicated variant, unreachable!(), or debug_assert! would be semantically correct. The comment's own reasoning ('not warranted') is insufficient justification for misclassified errors."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-cd84c211","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. run_id remains Option<&str> in TaskRunLineagePort (service.rs:103,117) and record_bead_start (service.rs:409). The model layer retains find_matching_running_task_run with runless .or_else() fallback (model.rs:495-500), and fs.rs retains unique_terminal_replay_match with runless guards (fs.rs:2829+). This means a bead CAN still be started without a run_id and later finalized by matching a runless row via started_at — exactly the ambiguity Issue 2 was supposed to eliminate. Legacy tests at model.rs:1031-1219 (six tests) actively codify this behavior. While overlapping with fr-19-a8837f43, this amendment provides actionable run_id-specific remediation."},{"amendment_id":"fr-19-9910b1f5","decision":"accept","rationale":"Verified. plan_hash remains Option<&str> in the service port (service.rs:97-105,401-437). The snapshot-derived backfill machinery is fully active: snapshot_plan_hash_at_creation field (model.rs:286-292), snapshot_plan_hash function (fs.rs:2554), safe_plan_hash_backfill function (fs.rs:2583-2624). Tests at service.rs:4727-4819 and 5756-5962 codify the snapshot-dependent behavior including safe backfill filling plan_hash when snapshot is unchanged. This means lineage rows derive plan_hash from mutable snapshot state rather than requiring the controller's dispatch-time hash, which is what Issue 3 asked to remove. While overlapping with fr-19-a8837f43, this provides plan_hash-specific remediation details."}]},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"9aed2f06-ae8f-41f1-9b0b-ca879e2c5466"}
